Rule.check:
To check if kernel core dumps are enabled, run the
    following command: sudo sysctl kern.coredump | awk '{ print $NF
    }' If the value is not '0', this is a finding.

Rule.fixtext:
To change the ownership of any finding, run the
    following command:sudo find / -type d -perm -1002 -not -uid 0
    -exec chown root {} \;

Run the following command to set the sticky bit on all
    world-writable directories:sudo find / -type d \( -perm -0002
    -a ! -perm -1000 \) -exec chmod +t {} \;
